gotsheep:
The gotsheep minigame can be started in the item menu, by clicking on the three flowers.
Flick the sheep to move it. To advance to the next phase you need to meet a point requirement. 
At the end of every wave you get one Shuusui, these stack, so use them when you can't meet point requirement / during final round.
There are 5 waves:
```
Wave | Border | Time | Score/E. | E. Size | E. Hits Required
1    |   2500 |   30 |       10 |      70 | 250
2    |   5000 |   35 |       20 |     100 | 250
3    |  15000 |   40 |       40 |      80 | 375
4    |  50000 |   45 |       80 |      90 | 625
5    |  70000 |   50 |      100 |     120 | 700
```
To get an S rank, you'll need to reach wave 5 and get 70000 points.

Example of S rank playthrough; <https://youtu.be/tERzplgdU1U>
kccp:
**KCCacheProxy**: <https://github.com/Tibowl/KCCacheProxy/releases/>

**Installation video**: <90s video showing how to install (& setup for Chrome) <https://youtu.be/Dog1zKAAWeI>

**Installation** (v2 or later, windows): Get latest setup exe from releases for your architecture (32/64 bit), open it, set browser/viewer proxy to localhost:8081, import the basic built-in cache dump
*(see <https://github.com/Tibowl/KCCacheProxy/wiki/Installation-and-setup#browserviewer-setup> for more information)*

**Full/differential cache dumps (optional)**: <http://shizuru.piro.moe/kccp/>
*Instructions on how to use cache dumps*: <https://github.com/Tibowl/KCCacheProxy/wiki/Installation-and-setup#using-cache-dumps>

**More information**: <https://github.com/Tibowl/KCCacheProxy/wiki>

**English Patch** (Add-on to KCCP managed by Oradimi#8947): <https://github.com/Oradimi/KanColle-English-Patch-KCCP>

If you need additional support for the English Patch or KCCacheProxy, please visit the KC English Patch Discord: <https://discord.gg/krMeMKB>
